Uses of Package
com.adonax.audiocue

  • Classes in com.adonax.audiocue used by com.adonax.audiocue 
    Class and Description
    AudioCue
    The AudioCue represents a segment of audio media that is loaded into memory prior to playback and which offers minimal latency, concurrent playback of instances, and real time controls for volume, panning and playback speed of each instance.
    AudioCue.PanType
    The enum Type is a repository of functions used to perform volume-based panning for stereo media.
    AudioCueInstanceEvent
    The AudioCueInstanceEvent class represents an event in the life cycle of an AudioCue instance.
    AudioCueInstanceEvent.Type
    The enum Type represents events that occur during the lifetime of an AudioCue instance.
    AudioCueListener
    A listener interface for receiving notifications of events pertaining to an AudioCue and its playable or playing instances.
    AudioMixer
    AudioMixer combines the output of members of an AudioMixerTrack collection into a single SourceDataLine output line.
    AudioMixerTrack
    AudioMixerTrack is the interface for tracks that are mixed in an AudioMixer.
